If you’re an Electro-mechanically-minded vehicle enthusiast with stellar customer service skills, this job is for you! Our dealership seeks an automotive service advisor who loves greeting customers, assessing customer needs and scheduling appointments for our capable service technicians. In this role, you’ll use your product knowledge as a service advisor and draft cost estimates, evaluate warranty protections, and coordinate necessary repairs. If you’re confident you’re the one we need to fill this promising position, apply now!

Service technician Responsibilities

  • Review and verify vehicle warranty protections and service contract coverage when developing cost estimates, work orders, and other paperwork related to necessary repairs
  • Leverage automotive technology and product knowledge to clearly address customer needs and share the status of service appointments
  • Schedule appointments for service technicians
  • Resolve customer complaints and make follow-up calls to facilitate a positive service center experience
  • Lead vehicle pick-up efforts by coordinating efforts with auto service porters and customers
  • Manage all automotive paperwork, including repair orders, invoices, and maintenance records

Service technician Qualifications

  • Have a ITI, Diploma or graduate.

  • Must have strong organizational, communications, and interpersonal skills
  • Oversee service team, auto service staff, and vehicle repair processes to deliver a positive service experience and maintain profitability
  • Ensure delivery of customers’ vehicles on time
  • Coach team members on ways to drive service sales, beneficial training program options, and customer service tactics
  • Work with the service advisor to ensure proactive resolution of all customer complaints and make follow-up calls, as needed
  • Maintain a high level of customer satisfaction in all automotive service capacities to increase retention and referrals
  • Oversee all day-to-day job duties within the automotive service department with a focus on high employee and customer morale
  • Guide the management of all automotive service department paperwork, including repair orders, invoices, and maintenance records

If you’re a high-performing sales representative with exemplary communication skills and a proven record of success, you might be perfect for our showroom sales representative position. We’ll reward your success with competitive bonuses, mentorship, and ongoing education opportunities. Strong interpersonal skills and prior sales experience are a must for this dynamic role. Be ready to greet guests on the showroom floor, answer questions, and coordinate test drives. Apply to be our showroom sales service support representative today to lift your skills to new heights!

 

Responsibilities:

  • Greet and assist customers entering the showroom floor to present a professional environment that supports automotive sales

  • Training personnel and helping team members develop their skills

  • Managing sales data, field support tools and dealer MIS

  • Excellent time management, organisation and presentation skills
  • MS office knowledge is necessary

Job Overview

We are interested in hiring a dedicated and hardworking individual as a Telecaller to join our Sales Department.

Your main goal is to boost our sales by reaching out to the existing customers as well as potential customers. As a Telecaller, you are responsible for handling sales over the phone entirely. You are also responsible for solving questions in regard to the product or service provided by the company.

In addition to this, you should collect desired information from the clients and maintain healthy relations with them. You are required to understand the customer’s requirements and demands and close the sales deal efficiently. You are also required to write down important information provided by the customer and follow up with them on a regular basis.

As an ideal candidate, you should be an excellent communicator along with convincing abilities. Great report writing skills, amazing negotiation skills, and phenomenal telephone etiquette are essential for this position.

If you are ready to take up these duties and responsibilities of Telecaller, then apply right away. We will love to meet you.

Responsibilities

  • Answering phones and explaining the product and services offered by the company.
  • Contacting existing customers as well as prospective customers using scripts.
  • Obtaining customer information and other relevant data.
  • Asking questions to the customer and understanding their specifications.
  • Resolving queries and issues related to the products and services.
  • Making recordings of all the sales phone calls and sales deals.
  • Taking and processing product orders in a professional manner.
  • Maintaining the database of the customers on a regular basis.
  • Suggesting solutions based on customer’s needs and requirements.

Area Sales Manager will be responsible for creating Sales Channel and managing existing Channel Partners to drive revenue growth. To Develop and manage efficient distribution networks for sales, monitoring sales team performance, analyzing sales data, periodical forecasting etc in their regions.

Role & Responsibilities:

1.       To create Distribution, Dealer and Sub-Dealer network.

2.       Develop Sales and marketing strategies to drive sales growth in the assigned area.

3.       Develop and manage an efficient distribution network to improve sales performance.

4.       Conduct market research to understand competitors and market trends.

5.       To create orders through Distributor & Dealer Network.

6.       Identifying the right customers and their decision makers to create sales in his region.

7.       Creating Sales along with good Brand Positioning in that Dist. /Dealer.

8.       To follow up for A/C Receivable, Inform accounts accordingly.

9.       Develop creative promotional strategies to attract more customers.

●        Minimum 5 years of Channel Sales experience in the respective territory.

●        Industry- Prefrable Having 2 Years Experience of Bathroom Fittings or Sanitaryware

●        Pleasing Personality, Consistency and Fluency in English or Hindi is mandatory.

●        Should be Graduate or Post Graduate in Sales, Marketing or any relevant degree.

●        Strong Market knowledge and Open to travel

●        Strong Communication and Presentation skills

●        Focused and result oriented

●        Self motivated and good leadership skills

  • Guide and help companies to post their job requirements on ShramIN jobs portal.

Tele Sales Executive

  • Job Type - Full Time
  • Location - Noida Sector 62
  • Salary - (12k - 18k) depends on your experience and knowledge


We are looking out for experienced and self driven telesales executive to join our sales team for ShramIN, a dedicated job site for blue & grey collar workforce needed in micro and small enterprises. It is a technology-based networking platform, built on three pillars - candidates, employers and training partners. As a Telesales Representative, you will be responsible for handling outgoing calls to employers and placement agencies; resolving their issues promptly and thoroughly. 


Job Responsibilities of Executive - Telesales

  • The role will include reaching out to placement agencies and small medium enterprises(SME) to present our service offerings.
  • Job is target based, where you have to onboard placement agencies and small medium enterprises (SME).
  • Collect data about various placement agencies and employers to meet further targets.
  • Ability To learn about our job portal Inside out so that you have thorough knowledge to guide and help the employers in rectifying their issue.
  • Your job will also involve taking feedback from employers and placement agencies. 
  • Guide and help companies to post their job requirements on ShramIN jobs portal. 
  • Build sustainable relationships and trust with employers through open and interactive communication.


Desired Candidate Profile -Qualifications & Skills

  • 1-2 years job experience in customer support. Prior experience in the same field will be an advantage.
  • Graduate in any stream.
  • Proficient in Hindi & English and interpersonal Skills.
  • Good working knowledge Of Excel/Word.
  • Ability to resolve issues and address complaints. Cool-tempered and able to handle rejection.


More details:

  • Working days Monday to Saturday.


Regards,

Anupam Sharma
